Mail-in-a-Box patch: frontend - subfolder hierarchy in folder sidebar
=====================================================================

Companion frontend patch to 1_miab_oxi_auth_patch.patch.

oxi's FolderTree rendered all IMAP folders as a flat list regardless of
nesting depth. IMAP supports hierarchical folder names using a per-folder
delimiter character (usually "/") returned by LIST — e.g. "Projects/Work"
is a child of "Projects". This patch teaches FolderTree to build and render
a proper tree.

Changes:
  - buildFolderTree(): converts the flat Folder[] API response into a
    sorted TreeNode tree using each folder's delimiter field. Parent nodes
    are found by lastIndexOf(delimiter); orphaned nodes (parent not in
    list) are promoted to roots.

  - FolderItem: gains depth (controls left indentation), hasChildren,
    isCollapsed, and onToggleCollapse props. The single-button layout is
    replaced with a two-button row (chevron toggle + nav button) so the
    collapse control and folder navigation are separate interactive elements
    as required by HTML (no nested buttons).

  - InlineRenameInput: gains displayName and parentPath props. The input
    field now shows only the last path segment; the full IMAP path is
    reconstructed on submit as parentPath + trimmed. The no-op guard
    compares against displayName (the pre-filled value) rather than the
    full folder name.

  - FolderTreeNodeItem: thin recursive renderer that renders FolderItem for
    a node and its children (when expanded).

  - FolderTree: adds collapsed Set state, a memoised tree build, and a
    toggleCollapsed callback.

  - \Noselect folders (IMAP path containers with no messages) cannot be
    navigated to and do not accept drag-drop targets. They get no context
    menu (rename/delete).

